the latest dlc was kind of a disaster
the game originally was made by a small indie studio called Hopoo games
They did a very good job with it, game was really fun, and had overwhelmingly positive reviews on steam
eventually the studio decided that they did everything they wanted with the franchise and sold the rights to IP to a gearbox
gearbox started working on a new dlc, did a bunch of hype, released animated trailers and stuff
so, at that point game worked very well, not a lot of bugs was very stable
PC version that is, console version had some issues

Gearbox had a brilliant idea, to get rid of the PC version code, and merge the code base with the console version. So they basically did a port from console to PC, even though they already had a working PC version, and now game is riddled with bugs
One of the most ridiculous things is that all of the game physics, movement and a lot of mechanics got tied to fps
so depending of how much fps you had, you could shoot faster, some of your abilities made you ridiculously fast
even the spawn manager somehow got tied to fps, and the enemy spawn rates were fps dependent
basically at the day of release the game was in unplayable state
and console players couldn't progress past the main menu, coz the new game button just didn't work
idk how much do you know about coding in Unity, but apparently they forgot Time.deltatime
